 According to him, Mr Soba’s removal was unanimously approved by the association’s National Executive Council, NEC, and the Board of Trustees, BOT at its all night meeting held on Wednesday in Asaba, Delta State. He said Mr Soba was removed based on misconduct against the constitutional provisions of ALGON after a  motion for Mr Soba’s removal at the meeting was raised by the Nasarawa State Chapter Chairman of ALGON, Aminu Maifata, who is also the chairman of Lafia LGA. He added that the motion was seconded by Delta State representative, Ikpokpo Malik, and the Sokoto State ALGON chairman, Aminu Ibrahim. 